  South Korea â€™s overseas borrowing
decreased to $360 billion at the end of 2010 as local banks
repaid loans, the Bank of Korea said.  Foreign debt fell from $365.9 billion three months earlier,
the central bank said in a statement today. Borrowing abroad
totaled $345.4 billion at the end of 2009.  Short-term debt due within a year dropped to $135 billion
from $145.3 billion three months earlier, while long-term
borrowing rose to $225 billion from $220.6 billion.  To contact the reporters on this story:
